data.name: ValidateKey.HelpString
data.value: Clicking this button will validate your Listen Key by contacting Digitally Imported's, JazzRadio's or SKY.FM's servers. RockRadio doesn't use Listen Keys so the Key will be validated against Digitally Imported's servers instead.

data.name: ListenLink.HelpString
data.value: Clicking this link will open your default web browser pointing to your My Listen Key page, where you'll be able to check your current Listen Key and reset it. RockRadio doesn't use Listen Keys so this link will open the Digitally Imported page instead.

data.name: FileFormat.HelpString
data.value: Select your preferred file format for listening to Digitally Imported, SKY.FM, RockRadio or JazzRadio. The following file formats are supported for FREE accounts: MP3 @ 96 kbits/sec, AAC-HE @ 40 kbits/sec, Windows Media @ 40 kbits/sec. The following formats are supported for PREMIUM accounts: MP3 @ 256 and 128 kbits/sec, AAC-HE @ 128, 64 and 40 kbits/sec, Windows Media @ 128 and 64 kbits/sec (Windows Media 64 kbits/sec not available for JazzRadio). Currently RockRadio is in Beta stage and they only support MP3 @ 96kbits/sec.

data.name: HighQualityVis.HelpString
data.value: Selecting this check box will apply an antialiasing effect on the visualisations that would be benefited by it. Please note that this option will use a lot of CPU so it's recommended that you leave it unchecked if you don't have a very powerful PC.

data.name: Label11.Text
data.value: You can set your own custom hotkeys to do several operations while the application is minimised to the tray area; to customise hotkeys simply select the check box of the action you want to set and then press your desired keys. To return to the default hotkey simply clear it.

data.name: AutoEq.HelpString
data.value: This button adjusts any equalizer settings so that no positive amplification is applied to any of the frequency bands, i.e. 0dB is the “highest” value. This may help reduce possible distortion without changing the “shape” of the frequency band, e.g. if +5dB is the highest level of amplification, all frequency bands are lowered by -5dB, so -8dB changes to -13dB and so on. Please note that you will have to raise your volume after applying this adjustment since the frequency response will be quieter.

data.value:

The Facebook, Twitter and Google logos are used according to their respective Terms of Use.
Integration with the AudioAddict API is thanks to _Tobias from the Digitally Imported Forums.
The developer of this application is in no way affiliated with Digitally Imported, JazzRadio, RockRadio, SKY.FM, the creators of the icons or the developers of the dlls.
This application is provided AS IS with no warranty.
Your Listen Key is only sent to the developer's hosting server when you click the "Validate" button and in order to retrieve your My Favorites playlist. You can always erase your Listen Key and use the Free streams on all radio stations. A Listen Key is not mandatory for the proper operation of this software. Your Listen Key is never stored on the server, after the validation and/or downloading processes finish no traces of your Listen Key are left on the server. The developer respects your privacy and will never use your Listen Key in a way that is not detailed here. If you want to know in detail what the application does with your Listen Key, a way of obtaining the source code of the software is detailed below.
If you think your Listen key may have been compromised, please go to http://www.di.fm/member/listen_key or http://www.jazzradio.com/member/listen_key or http://www.sky.fm/member/listen_key
to get a new one and change your password at https://www.di.fm/member/profile or https://www.jazzradio.com/member/profile or https://www.sky.fm/member/profile
This application is open source! Head over to https://github.com/ViRUS2012/DIRadio to download the complete source code, make comments, suggestions, or to submit your own improvements!
